88 void RigSpawner::Setup(
89  Beam *rig,
90  boost::shared_ptr<RigDef::File> file,
91  Ogre::SceneNode *parent,
92  Ogre::Vector3 const & spawn_position,
93  Ogre::Quaternion const & spawn_rotation,
94  int cache_entry_number
95 )
96 {
97  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
98 
99  m_rig = rig;
100  m_file = file;
101  m_cache_entry_number = cache_entry_number;
102  m_parent_scene_node = parent;
103  m_spawn_position = spawn_position;
104  m_spawn_rotation = spawn_rotation;
105  m_current_keyword = RigDef::File::KEYWORD_INVALID;
106  m_enable_background_loading = BSETTING("Background Loading", false);
107  m_wing_area = 0.f;
108  m_fuse_z_min = 1000.0f;
109  m_fuse_z_max = -1000.0f;
110  m_fuse_y_min = 1000.0f;
111  m_fuse_y_max = -1000.0f;
112 
113  m_generate_wing_position_lights = true;
114  // TODO: Handle modules
115  if (file->root_module->engine.get() != nullptr) // Engine present => it's a land vehicle.
116  {
117  m_generate_wing_position_lights = false; // Disable aerial pos. lights for land vehicles.
118  }
119 
120  // add custom include path
121  if (!SSETTING("resourceIncludePath", "").empty())
122  {
123  Ogre::ResourceGroupManager::getSingleton().addResourceLocation(
124  SSETTING("resourceIncludePath", ""),
125  "FileSystem",
126  "customInclude"
127  );
128  }
129 
130  // initialize custom include path
131  if (!SSETTING("resourceIncludePath", "").empty())
132  {
133  Ogre::ResourceBackgroundQueue::getSingleton().initialiseResourceGroup("customInclude");
134  }
135 
136  m_messages_num_errors = 0;
137  m_messages_num_warnings = 0;
138  m_messages_num_other = 0;
139 }

470 void RigSpawner::FinalizeRig()
471 {
472  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
473 
474  // we should post-process the torque curve if existing
475  if (m_rig->engine)
476  {
477  int result = m_rig->engine->getTorqueCurve()->spaceCurveEvenly(m_rig->engine->getTorqueCurve()->getUsedSpline());
478  if (result)
479  {
480  m_rig->engine->getTorqueCurve()->setTorqueModel("default");
481  if (result == 1)
482  {
483  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "TorqueCurve: Points (rpm) must be in an ascending order. Using default curve");
484  }
485  }
486 
487  //Gearbox
488  m_rig->engine->setAutoMode(Settings::getSingleton().GetGearBoxMode());
489  }
490 
491  //calculate gwps height offset
492  //get a starting value
493  m_rig->posnode_spawn_height=m_rig->nodes[0].RelPosition.y;
494  //start at 0 to avoid a crash whith a 1-node truck
495  for (int i=0; i<m_rig->free_node; i++)
496  {
497  // scan and store the y-coord for the lowest node of the truck
498  if (m_rig->nodes[i].RelPosition.y <= m_rig->posnode_spawn_height)
499  {
500  m_rig->posnode_spawn_height = m_rig->nodes[i].RelPosition.y;
501  }
502  }
503 
504  if (m_rig->cameranodepos[0] > 0)
505  {
506  // store the y-difference between the trucks lowest node and the campos-node for the gwps system
507  m_rig->posnode_spawn_height = m_rig->nodes[m_rig->cameranodepos[0]].RelPosition.y - m_rig->posnode_spawn_height;
508  }
509  else
510  {
511  //this can not be an airplane, just set it to 0.
512  m_rig->posnode_spawn_height = 0.0f;
513  }
514 
515  //cameras workaround
516  for (int i=0; i<m_rig->freecamera; i++)
517  {
518  //LogManager::getSingleton().logMessage("Camera dir="+StringConverter::toString(nodes[cameranodedir[i]].RelPosition-nodes[cameranodepos[i]].RelPosition)+" roll="+StringConverter::toString(nodes[cameranoderoll[i]].RelPosition-nodes[cameranodepos[i]].RelPosition));
519  Ogre::Vector3 dir_node_offset = GetNode(m_rig->cameranodedir[i]).RelPosition - GetNode(m_rig->cameranodepos[i]).RelPosition;
520  Ogre::Vector3 roll_node_offset = GetNode(m_rig->cameranoderoll[i]).RelPosition - GetNode(m_rig->cameranodepos[i]).RelPosition;
521  Ogre::Vector3 cross = dir_node_offset.crossProduct(roll_node_offset);
522 
523  m_rig->revroll[i]=cross.y > 0;//(nodes[cameranodedir[i]].RelPosition-nodes[cameranodepos[i]].RelPosition).crossProduct(nodes[cameranoderoll[i]].RelPosition-nodes[cameranodepos[i]].RelPosition).y>0;
524  if (m_rig->revroll[i])
525  {
526  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "camera definition is probably invalid and has been corrected. It should be center, back, left");
527  }
528  }
529 
530  //wing closure
531  if (m_rig->wingstart!=-1)
532  {
533  if (m_rig->autopilot != nullptr)
534  {
535  m_rig->autopilot->setInertialReferences(
536  & GetNode(m_airplane_left_light),
537  & GetNode(m_airplane_right_light),
538  m_rig->fuseBack,
539  & GetNode(m_rig->cameranodepos[0])
540  );
541  }
542  //inform wing segments
543  float span=GetNode(m_rig->wings[m_rig->wingstart].fa->nfrd).RelPosition.distance(GetNode(m_rig->wings[m_rig->free_wing-1].fa->nfld).RelPosition);
544 
545  //parser_warning(c, "Full Wing "+TOSTRING(wingstart)+"-"+TOSTRING(free_wing-1)+" SPAN="+TOSTRING(span)+" AREA="+TOSTRING(wingarea), PARSER_INFO);
546  m_rig->wings[m_rig->wingstart].fa->enableInducedDrag(span,m_wing_area, false);
547  m_rig->wings[m_rig->free_wing-1].fa->enableInducedDrag(span,m_wing_area, true);
548  //wash calculator
549  WashCalculator(m_spawn_rotation);
550  }
551  //add the cab visual
552  if (m_rig->free_texcoord>0 && m_rig->free_cab>0)
553  {
554  //closure
555  m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_texcoord;
556  m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_cab;
557  char wname[256];
558  sprintf(wname, "cab-%s",m_rig->truckname);
559  char wnamei[256];
560  sprintf(wnamei, "cabobj-%s",m_rig->truckname);
561  //the cab materials are as follow:
562  //texname: base texture with emissive(2 pass) or without emissive if none available(1 pass), alpha cutting
563  //texname-trans: transparency texture (1 pass)
564  //texname-back: backface texture: black+alpha cutting (1 pass)
565  //texname-noem: base texture without emissive (1 pass), alpha cutting
566 
567  //material passes must be:
568  //0: normal texture
569  //1: transparent (windows)
570  //2: emissive
571  /*strcpy(texname, "testtex");
572  char transmatname[256];
573  sprintf(transmatname, "%s-trans", texname);
574  char backmatname[256];
575  sprintf(backmatname, "%s-back", texname);
576  hasEmissivePass=1;*/
577 
578  Ogre::MaterialPtr mat=Ogre::MaterialManager::getSingleton().getByName(m_rig->texname);
579  if (mat.isNull())
580  {
581 
582 #ifdef USE_MYGUI
583  RoR::Console *console = RoR::Application::GetConsole();
584  if (console) console->putMessage(
585  Console::CONSOLE_MSGTYPE_INFO,
586  Console::CONSOLE_SYSTEM_ERROR,
587  "unable to load vehicle (Material '"+Ogre::String(m_rig->texname)+"' missing!): " + m_rig->realtruckname,
588  "error.png",
589  30000,
590  true
591  );
592  RoR::Application::GetGuiManager()->PushNotification("Notice:", "unable to load vehicle (Material '" + Ogre::String(m_rig->texname) + "' missing!): " + m_rig->realtruckname);
593 #endif // USE_MYGUI
594 
595  Ogre::String msg = "Material '"+Ogre::String(m_rig->texname)+"' missing!";
596  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg);
597  return;
598  }
599 
600  //-trans
601  char transmatname[256];
602  sprintf(transmatname, "%s-trans", m_rig->texname);
603  Ogre::MaterialPtr transmat=mat->clone(transmatname);
604  if (mat->getTechnique(0)->getNumPasses()>1)
605  {
606  transmat->getTechnique(0)->removePass(1);
607  }
608  transmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->setAlphaRejectSettings(Ogre::CMPF_LESS_EQUAL, 128);
609  transmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->setDepthWriteEnabled(false);
610  if (transmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->getNumTextureUnitStates()>0)
611  {
612  transmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->getTextureUnitState(0)->setTextureFiltering(Ogre::TFO_NONE);
613  }
614  transmat->compile();
615 
616  //-back
617  char backmatname[256];
618  sprintf(backmatname, "%s-back", m_rig->texname);
619  Ogre::MaterialPtr backmat=mat->clone(backmatname);
620  if (mat->getTechnique(0)->getNumPasses()>1)
621  {
622  backmat->getTechnique(0)->removePass(1);
623  }
624  if (transmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->getNumTextureUnitStates()>0)
625  {
626  backmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->getTextureUnitState(0)->setColourOperationEx(
627  Ogre::LBX_SOURCE1,
628  Ogre::LBS_MANUAL,
629  Ogre::LBS_MANUAL,
630  Ogre::ColourValue(0,0,0),
631  Ogre::ColourValue(0,0,0)
632  );
633  }
634  if (m_rig->shadowOptimizations)
635  {
636  backmat->setReceiveShadows(false);
637  }
638  //just in case
639  //backmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->setSceneBlending(SBT_TRANSPARENT_ALPHA);
640  //backmat->getTechnique(0)->getPass(0)->setAlphaRejectSettings(CMPF_GREATER, 128);
641  backmat->compile();
642 
643  //-noem and -noem-trans
644  if (mat->getTechnique(0)->getNumPasses()>1)
645  {
646  m_rig->hasEmissivePass=1;
647  char clomatname[256];
648  sprintf(clomatname, "%s-noem", m_rig->texname);
649  Ogre::MaterialPtr clomat=mat->clone(clomatname);
650  clomat->getTechnique(0)->removePass(1);
651  clomat->compile();
652  }
653 
654  //base texture is not modified
655  // mat->compile();
656 
657 
658  //parser_warning(c, "creating mesh", PARSER_INFO);
659  m_rig->cabMesh =new FlexObj(
660  m_rig->nodes,
661  m_rig->free_texcoord,
662  m_rig->texcoords,
663  m_rig->free_cab,
664  m_rig->cabs,
665  m_rig->free_sub,
666  m_rig->subtexcoords,
667  m_rig->subcabs,
668  m_rig->texname,
669  wname,
670  m_rig->subisback,
671  backmatname,
672  transmatname
673  );
674  //parser_warning(c, "creating entity", PARSER_INFO);
675 
676 
677  //parser_warning(c, "creating cabnode", PARSER_INFO);
678  m_rig->cabNode = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
679  Ogre::Entity *ec = nullptr;
680  try
681  {
682  //parser_warning(c, "loading cab", PARSER_INFO);
683  ec = gEnv->sceneManager->createEntity(wnamei, wname);
684  // ec->setRenderQueueGroup(RENDER_QUEUE_6);
685  //parser_warning(c, "attaching cab", PARSER_INFO);
686  if (ec)
687  {
688  m_rig->deletion_Entities.emplace_back(ec);
689  m_rig->cabNode->attachObject(ec);
690  }
691  } catch(...)
692  {
693  //parser_warning(c, "error loading mesh: "+String(wname));
694  Ogre::String msg = "error loading mesh: "+Ogre::String(wname);
695  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg);
696  }
697  MaterialFunctionMapper::replaceSimpleMeshMaterials(ec, Ogre::ColourValue(0.5, 1, 0.5));
698  if (m_rig->materialFunctionMapper != nullptr)
699  {
700  m_rig->materialFunctionMapper->replaceMeshMaterials(ec);
701  }
702  if (m_rig->materialReplacer != nullptr)
703  {
704  m_rig->materialReplacer->replaceMeshMaterials(ec);
705  }
706  if (m_rig->usedSkin != nullptr)
707  {
708  m_rig->usedSkin->replaceMeshMaterials(ec);
709  }
710 
711  };
712  //parser_warning(c, "cab ok", PARSER_INFO);
713  // mWindow->setDebugText("Beam number:"+ TOSTRING(free_beam));
714 /*
715  if (c.mode == BTS_DESCRIPTION)
716  parser_warning(c, "description section not closed with end_description", PARSER_ERROR);
717 
718  if (c.mode == BTS_COMMENT)
719  parser_warning(c, "comment section not closed with end_comment", PARSER_ERROR);
720 
721  if (c.mode == BTS_SECTION)
722  parser_warning(c, "section section not closed with end_section", PARSER_ERROR);
723 */
724  // check for some things
725  if (strnlen(m_rig->guid, 128) == 0)
726  {
727  //parser_warning(c, "vehicle uses no GUID, skinning will be impossible", PARSER_OBSOLETE);
728  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "vehicle uses no GUID, skinning will be impossible");
729  }
730 
731  m_rig->lowestnode = FindLowestNodeInRig();
732 
733  UpdateCollcabContacterNodes();
734 
735  m_flex_factory.SaveFlexbodiesToCache();
736 
737 #if 0 // hashing + scope_log disabled
738 
739  // now generate the hash of it
740  {
741  // copy whole truck into a string
742  Ogre::String code;
743  ds->seek(0); // from start
744  code.resize(ds->size());
745  ds->read(&code[0], ds->size());
746 
747  // and build the hash over it
748  char hash_result[250];
749  memset(hash_result, 0, 249);
750  RoR::CSHA1 sha1;
751  sha1.UpdateHash((uint8_t *)code.c_str(), (uint32_t)code.size());
752  sha1.Final();
753  sha1.ReportHash(hash_result, RoR::CSHA1::REPORT_HEX_SHORT);
754  beamHash = String(hash_result);
755  }
756 
757 
758 
759 
760  // WARNING: this must come LAST
761  if (!SSETTING("vehicleOutputFile", "").empty())
762  {
763  // serialize the truck in a special format :)
764  String fn = SSETTING("vehicleOutputFile", "");
765  serialize(fn, &scope_log);
766  }
767 
768 #endif
769 }

780 void RigSpawner::WashCalculator(Ogre::Quaternion const & rot)
781 {
782  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
783 
784  Ogre::Quaternion invrot=rot.Inverse();
785  //we will compute wash
786  int w,p;
787  for (p=0; p<m_rig->free_aeroengine; p++)
788  {
789  Ogre::Vector3 prop=invrot*m_rig->nodes[m_rig->aeroengines[p]->getNoderef()].RelPosition;
790  float radius=m_rig->aeroengines[p]->getRadius();
791  for (w=0; w<m_rig->free_wing; w++)
792  {
793  //left wash
794  Ogre::Vector3 wcent=invrot*((m_rig->nodes[m_rig->wings[w].fa->nfld].RelPosition+m_rig->nodes[m_rig->wings[w].fa->nfrd].RelPosition)/2.0);
795  //check if wing is near enough along X (less than 15m back)
796  if (wcent.x>prop.x && wcent.x<prop.x+15.0)
797  {
798  //check if it's okay vertically
799  if (wcent.y>prop.y-radius && wcent.y<prop.y+radius)
800  {
801  //okay, compute wash coverage ratio along Z
802  float wleft=(invrot*m_rig->nodes[m_rig->wings[w].fa->nfld].RelPosition).z;
803  float wright=(invrot*m_rig->nodes[m_rig->wings[w].fa->nfrd].RelPosition).z;
804  float pleft=prop.z+radius;
805  float pright=prop.z-radius;
806  float aleft=wleft;
807  if (pleft<aleft) aleft=pleft;
808  float aright=wright;
809  if (pright>aright) aright=pright;
810  if (aright<aleft)
811  {
812  //we have a wash
813  float wratio=(aleft-aright)/(wleft-wright);
814  m_rig->wings[w].fa->addwash(p, wratio);
815  Ogre::String msg = "Wing "+TOSTRING(w)+" is washed by prop "+TOSTRING(p)+" at "+TOSTRING((float)(wratio*100.0))+"%";
816  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_INFO, msg);
817  }
818  }
819  }
820  }
821  }
822 }

824 void RigSpawner::ProcessTurbojet(RigDef::Turbojet & def)
825 {
826  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
827 
828  int front,back,ref;
829  front = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.front_node);//parse_node_number(c, args[0]);
830  back = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.back_node);//parse_node_number(c, args[1]);
831  ref = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.side_node);//parse_node_number(c, args[2]);
832 
833  char propname[256];
834  sprintf(propname, "turbojet-%s-%i", m_rig->truckname, m_rig->free_aeroengine);
835  Turbojet *tj=new Turbojet(
836  propname,
837  m_rig->free_aeroengine,
838  m_rig->trucknum,
839  m_rig->nodes,
840  front,
841  back,
842  ref,
843  def.dry_thrust, //drthrust,
844  def.is_reversable != 0, //rev!=0,
845  def.wet_thrust > 0, //abthrust>0,
846  def.wet_thrust, //abthrust,
847  def.front_diameter,
848  def.back_diameter, //bdiam,
849  def.nozzle_length, //len,
850  m_rig->disable_smoke,
851  m_rig->heathaze,
852  m_rig->materialFunctionMapper,
853  m_rig->usedSkin,
854  m_rig->materialReplacer);
855 
856  m_rig->aeroengines[m_rig->free_aeroengine]=tj;
857  m_rig->driveable=AIRPLANE;
858  if (m_rig->autopilot == nullptr && m_rig->state != NETWORKED)
859  m_rig->autopilot=new Autopilot(m_rig->trucknum);
860  //if (audio) audio->setupAeroengines(TURBOJETS);
861 
862  m_rig->free_aeroengine++;
863 }

873 void RigSpawner::ProcessScrewprop(RigDef::Screwprop & def)

898 void RigSpawner::ProcessFusedrag(RigDef::Fusedrag & def)
899 {
900  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
901 
902  //parse fusedrag
903  int front_node_idx = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.front_node);
904  int back_node_idx = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.rear_node);
905  float width = 1.f;
906  float factor = 1.f;
907  char fusefoil[256];
908  strncpy(fusefoil, def.airfoil_name.c_str(), 255);
909 
910  if (def.autocalc)
911  {
912  // fusedrag autocalculation
913 
914  // calculate fusedrag by truck size
915  factor = def.area_coefficient;
916  width = (m_fuse_z_max - m_fuse_z_min) * (m_fuse_y_max - m_fuse_y_min) * factor;
917 
918  m_rig->fuseAirfoil = new Airfoil(fusefoil);
919 
920  m_rig->fuseFront = & GetNode(front_node_idx);
921  m_rig->fuseBack = & GetNode(front_node_idx); // This equals v0.38 / v0.4.0.7, but it's probably a bug
922  m_rig->fuseWidth = width;
923  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_INFO, "Fusedrag autocalculation size: "+TOSTRING(width)+" m^2");
924  } else
925  {
926  // original fusedrag calculation
927 
928  width = def.approximate_width;
929 
930  m_rig->fuseAirfoil = new Airfoil(fusefoil);
931 
932  m_rig->fuseFront = & GetNode(front_node_idx);
933  m_rig->fuseBack = & GetNode(front_node_idx); // This equals v0.38 / v0.4.0.7, but it's probably a bug
934  m_rig->fuseWidth = width;
935  }
936 }

938 void RigSpawner::BuildAerialEngine(
939  int ref_node_index,
940  int back_node_index,
941  int blade_1_node_index,
942  int blade_2_node_index,
943  int blade_3_node_index,
944  int blade_4_node_index,
945  int couplenode_index,
946  bool is_turboprops,
947  Ogre::String const & airfoil,
948  float power,
949  float pitch
950  )
951 {
952  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
953 
954  char propname[256];
955  sprintf(propname, "turboprop-%s-%i", m_rig->truckname, m_rig->free_aeroengine);
956 
957  Turboprop *turbo_prop = new Turboprop(
958  propname,
959  m_rig->nodes,
960  ref_node_index,
961  back_node_index,
962  blade_1_node_index,
963  blade_2_node_index,
964  blade_3_node_index,
965  blade_4_node_index,
966  couplenode_index,
967  power,
968  airfoil,
969  m_rig->free_aeroengine,
970  m_rig->trucknum,
971  m_rig->disable_smoke,
972  ! is_turboprops,
973  pitch,
974  m_rig->heathaze
975  );
976  m_rig->aeroengines[m_rig->free_aeroengine] = turbo_prop;
977  m_rig->free_aeroengine++;
978  m_rig->driveable = AIRPLANE;
979 
980  /* Autopilot */
981  if (m_rig->autopilot == nullptr && m_rig->state != NETWORKED)
982  {
983  m_rig->autopilot = new Autopilot(m_rig->trucknum);
984  }
985 
986  /* Visuals */
987  float scale = GetNode(ref_node_index).RelPosition.distance(GetNode(blade_1_node_index).RelPosition) / 2.25f;
988  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < static_cast<unsigned int>(m_rig->free_prop); i++)
989  {
990  prop_t & prop = m_rig->props[i];
991  if (prop.noderef == ref_node_index)
992  {
993  if (prop.pale == 1)
994  {
995  prop.snode->scale(scale, scale, scale);
996  turbo_prop->addPale(prop.snode);
997  }
998  if (prop.spinner == 1)
999  {
1000  prop.snode->scale(scale, scale, scale);
1001  turbo_prop->addSpinner(prop.snode);
1002  }
1003  }
1004  }
1005 }

1020  couple_node_index,

1024  -10
1025  );

1080 void RigSpawner::ProcessWing(RigDef::Wing & def)
1081 {
1082  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1083 
1084  if (! CheckWingLimit(1))
1085  {
1086  return;
1087  }
1088 
1089  std::stringstream wing_name;
1090  wing_name << "wing-" << m_rig->truckname << "-" << m_rig->free_wing;
1091  std::stringstream wing_obj_name;
1092  wing_obj_name << "wingobj-" << m_rig->truckname << "-" << m_rig->free_wing;
1093 
1094  unsigned int wing_index = m_rig->free_wing;
1095  m_rig->free_wing++;
1096  wing_t & wing = m_rig->wings[wing_index];
1097 
1098  int node_indices[8];
1099  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < 8; i++)
1100  {
1101  node_indices[i] = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.nodes[i]);
1102  }
1103 
1104  wing.fa = new FlexAirfoil(
1105  wing_name.str(),
1106  m_rig->nodes,
1107  node_indices[0],
1108  node_indices[1],
1109  node_indices[2],
1110  node_indices[3],
1111  node_indices[4],
1112  node_indices[5],
1113  node_indices[6],
1114  node_indices[7],
1115  m_rig->texname,
1116  Ogre::Vector2(def.tex_coords[0], def.tex_coords[1]),
1117  Ogre::Vector2(def.tex_coords[2], def.tex_coords[3]),
1118  Ogre::Vector2(def.tex_coords[4], def.tex_coords[5]),
1119  Ogre::Vector2(def.tex_coords[6], def.tex_coords[7]),
1120  def.control_surface,
1121  def.chord_point,
1122  def.min_deflection,
1123  def.max_deflection,
1124  def.airfoil,
1125  def.efficacy_coef,
1126  m_rig->aeroengines,
1127  m_rig->state != NETWORKED
1128  );
1129 
1130  Ogre::Entity *entity = nullptr;
1131  try
1132  {
1133  entity = gEnv->sceneManager->createEntity(wing_obj_name.str(), wing_name.str());
1134  }
1135  catch (...)
1136  {
1137  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Failed to load mesh (flexbody wing): " + wing_name.str());
1138  // Revert wing processing
1139  delete wing.fa;
1140  std::memset(&wing, 0, sizeof(wing));
1141  --m_rig->free_wing;
1142  return;
1143  }
1144  m_rig->deletion_Entities.emplace_back(entity);
1145  MaterialFunctionMapper::replaceSimpleMeshMaterials(entity, Ogre::ColourValue(0.5, 1, 0));
1146  if (m_rig->materialFunctionMapper)
1147  {
1148  m_rig->materialFunctionMapper->replaceMeshMaterials(entity);
1149  }
1150  if (m_rig->materialReplacer)
1151  {
1152  m_rig->materialReplacer->replaceMeshMaterials(entity);
1153  }
1154  if (m_rig->usedSkin)
1155  {
1156  m_rig->usedSkin->replaceMeshMaterials(entity);
1157  }
1158  wing.cnode = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
1159  wing.cnode->attachObject(entity);
1160 
1161  //induced drag
1162  if (m_rig->wingstart==-1)
1163  {
1164  m_rig->wingstart=wing_index;
1165  m_wing_area=ComputeWingArea(
1166  GetNode(wing.fa->nfld).AbsPosition,
1167  GetNode(wing.fa->nfrd).AbsPosition,
1168  GetNode(wing.fa->nbld).AbsPosition,
1169  GetNode(wing.fa->nbrd).AbsPosition
1170  );
1171  }
1172  else
1173  {
1174  wing_t & previous_wing = m_rig->wings[wing_index - 1];
1175  if (previous_wing.fa == nullptr)
1176  {
1177  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Unable to process wing, previous wing has no Airfoil");
1178  // Revert wing processing
1179  delete wing.fa;
1180  std::memset(&wing, 0, sizeof(wing));
1181  --m_rig->free_wing;
1182  return;
1183  }
1184 
1185  if (node_indices[1] != previous_wing.fa->nfld)
1186  {
1187  wing_t & start_wing = m_rig->wings[m_rig->wingstart];
1188 
1189  //discontinuity
1190  //inform wing segments
1191  float span = GetNode( start_wing.fa->nfrd).RelPosition.distance( GetNode(previous_wing.fa->nfld).RelPosition );
1192 
1193  start_wing.fa->enableInducedDrag(span, m_wing_area, false);
1194  previous_wing.fa->enableInducedDrag(span, m_wing_area, true);
1195 
1196  //we want also to add positional lights for first wing
1197  if (m_generate_wing_position_lights && m_rig->flaresMode>0)
1198  {
1199  if (! CheckPropLimit(4))
1200  {
1201  return;
1202  }
1203 
1204  //Left green
1205  m_airplane_left_light=previous_wing.fa->nfld;
1206  prop_t & left_green_prop = m_rig->props[m_rig->free_prop];
1207  m_rig->free_prop++;
1208 
1209  left_green_prop.noderef=previous_wing.fa->nfld;
1210  left_green_prop.nodex=previous_wing.fa->nflu;
1211  left_green_prop.nodey=previous_wing.fa->nfld; //ignored
1212  left_green_prop.offsetx=0.5;
1213  left_green_prop.offsety=0.0;
1214  left_green_prop.offsetz=0.0;
1215  left_green_prop.rot=Ogre::Quaternion::IDENTITY;
1216  left_green_prop.wheel=nullptr;
1217  left_green_prop.wheelrotdegree=0.0;
1218  left_green_prop.mirror=0;
1219  left_green_prop.pale=0;
1220  left_green_prop.spinner=0;
1221  left_green_prop.snode=nullptr; //no visible prop
1222  left_green_prop.bpos[0]=0.0;
1223  left_green_prop.brate[0]=1.0;
1224  left_green_prop.beacontype='L';
1225  left_green_prop.light[0]=nullptr; //no light
1226  //the flare billboard
1227  char propname[256];
1228  sprintf(propname, "prop-%s-%i", m_rig->truckname, m_rig->free_prop);
1229  left_green_prop.bbsnode[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
1230  left_green_prop.bbs[0]=gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(propname,1);
1231  left_green_prop.bbs[0]->createBillboard(0,0,0);
1232  if (left_green_prop.bbs[0])
1233  {
1234  left_green_prop.bbs[0]->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
1235  left_green_prop.bbs[0]->setMaterialName("tracks/greenflare");
1236  left_green_prop.bbsnode[0]->attachObject(left_green_prop.bbs[0]);
1237  }
1238  left_green_prop.bbsnode[0]->setVisible(false);
1239  left_green_prop.bbs[0]->setDefaultDimensions(0.5, 0.5);
1240  left_green_prop.animFlags[0]=0;
1241  left_green_prop.animMode[0]=0;
1242 
1243  //Left flash
1244  prop_t & left_flash_prop = m_rig->props[m_rig->free_prop];
1245  m_rig->free_prop++;
1246 
1247  left_flash_prop.noderef=previous_wing.fa->nbld;
1248  left_flash_prop.nodex=previous_wing.fa->nblu;
1249  left_flash_prop.nodey=previous_wing.fa->nbld; //ignored
1250  left_flash_prop.offsetx=0.5;
1251  left_flash_prop.offsety=0.0;
1252  left_flash_prop.offsetz=0.0;
1253  left_flash_prop.rot=Ogre::Quaternion::IDENTITY;
1254  left_flash_prop.wheel=nullptr;
1255  left_flash_prop.wheelrotdegree=0.0;
1256  left_flash_prop.mirror=0;
1257  left_flash_prop.pale=0;
1258  left_flash_prop.spinner=0;
1259  left_flash_prop.snode=nullptr; //no visible prop
1260  left_flash_prop.bpos[0]=0.5; //alt
1261  left_flash_prop.brate[0]=1.0;
1262  left_flash_prop.beacontype='w';
1263  //light
1264  sprintf(propname, "prop-%s-%i", m_rig->truckname, m_rig->free_prop);
1265  left_flash_prop.light[0]=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(propname);
1266  left_flash_prop.light[0]->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_POINT);

1268  left_flash_prop.light[0]->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 1.0, 1.0));
1269  left_flash_prop.light[0]->setAttenuation(50.0, 1.0, 0.3, 0.0);
1270  left_flash_prop.light[0]->setCastShadows(false);
1271  left_flash_prop.light[0]->setVisible(false);
1272  //the flare billboard
1273  left_flash_prop.bbsnode[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
1274  left_flash_prop.bbs[0]=gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(propname,1);
1275  left_flash_prop.bbs[0]->createBillboard(0,0,0);
1276  if (left_flash_prop.bbs[0])
1277  {
1278  left_flash_prop.bbs[0]->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
1279  left_flash_prop.bbs[0]->setMaterialName("tracks/flare");
1280  left_flash_prop.bbsnode[0]->attachObject(left_flash_prop.bbs[0]);
1281  }

1368  m_generate_wing_position_lights = false; // Already done
1369  }

1371  m_rig->wingstart=wing_index;
1372  m_wing_area=ComputeWingArea(
1373  GetNode(wing.fa->nfld).AbsPosition,
1374  GetNode(wing.fa->nfrd).AbsPosition,

1385  GetNode(wing.fa->nbrd).AbsPosition
1386  );
1387  }
1388  }

1391 float RigSpawner::ComputeWingArea(Ogre::Vector3 const & ref, Ogre::Vector3 const & x, Ogre::Vector3 const & y, Ogre::Vector3 const & aref)
1392 {
1393  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1394 
1395  return (((x-ref).crossProduct(y-ref)).length()+((x-aref).crossProduct(y-aref)).length())*0.5f;
1396 }

1497 void RigSpawner::ProcessGuiSettings(RigDef::GuiSettings & def)

1516  m_rig->speedoMax = RigDef::GuiSettings::DEFAULT_SPEEDO_MAX;
1517  }
1518  m_rig->useMaxRPMforGUI = def.use_max_rpm; /* Handles default */
1519 
1520  std::list<Ogre::String>::iterator dash_itor = def.dashboard_layouts.begin();
1521  for ( ; dash_itor != def.dashboard_layouts.end(); dash_itor++)
1522  {
1523  m_rig->dashBoardLayouts.push_back(std::pair<Ogre::String, bool>(*dash_itor, false));
1524  }
1525 
1526  std::list<Ogre::String>::iterator rtt_itor = def.rtt_dashboard_layouts.begin();
1527  for ( ; rtt_itor != def.rtt_dashboard_layouts.end(); rtt_itor++)
1528  {
1529  m_rig->dashBoardLayouts.push_back(std::pair<Ogre::String, bool>(*rtt_itor, true));
1530  }
1531 
1532 }

1540 void RigSpawner::ProcessExhaust(RigDef::Exhaust & def)
1541 {
1542  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1543 
1544  // parse exhausts
1545  if (m_rig->disable_smoke)
1546  {
1547  return;
1548  }
1549 
1550  node_t & ref_node = GetNodeOrThrow(def.reference_node);//id1;
1551  node_t & dir_node = GetNodeOrThrow(def.direction_node);//id2;
1552 
1553  exhaust_t exhaust;
1554  exhaust.emitterNode = ref_node.pos;
1555  exhaust.directionNode = dir_node.pos;
1556  exhaust.isOldFormat = false;
1557  exhaust.factor = 1.f; // Unused, according to wiki documentation.
1558  std::memset(exhaust.material, 0, sizeof(exhaust.material));
1559 
1560  exhaust.smokeNode = m_parent_scene_node->createChildSceneNode();
1561  std::stringstream instance_name;
1562  instance_name << "exhaust-" << m_rig->exhausts.size() << "-" << m_rig->truckname;
1563  Ogre::String material_name;
1564  if (def.material_name.empty() || def.material_name == "default")
1565  {
1566  material_name = "tracks/Smoke";
1567  }
1568  else
1569  {
1570  material_name = def.material_name;
1571  }
1572 
1573  if (m_rig->usedSkin)
1574  {
1575  Ogre::String newMat = m_rig->usedSkin->getReplacementForMaterial(material_name);
1576  if (!newMat.empty())
1577  {
1578  //strncpy(material, newMat.c_str(), 50);
1579  material_name = newMat;
1580  }
1581  }
1582 
1583  exhaust.smoker = gEnv->sceneManager->createParticleSystem(instance_name.str(), material_name);
1584  if (!exhaust.smoker)
1585  {
1586  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Failed to create exhaust particle system");
1587  return;
1588  }
1589  exhaust.smoker->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED); // disable particles in depthmap
1590  exhaust.smokeNode->attachObject(exhaust.smoker);
1591  exhaust.smokeNode->setPosition(m_rig->nodes[exhaust.emitterNode].AbsPosition);
1592 
1593  ref_node.isHot=true;
1594  dir_node.isHot=true;
1595  ref_node.iIsSkin=true;
1596  dir_node.iIsSkin=true;
1597  m_rig->exhausts.push_back(exhaust);
1598 }

1600 void RigSpawner::ProcessSubmeshGroundmodel()
1601 {
1602  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1603 
1604  SetCurrentKeyword(RigDef::File::KEYWORD_SUBMESH_GROUNDMODEL);
1605 
1606  auto module_itor = m_selected_modules.begin();
1607  auto module_end = m_selected_modules.end();
1608  for (; module_itor != module_end; ++module_itor)
1609  {
1610  if (! module_itor->get()->submeshes_ground_model_name.empty())
1611  {
1612  m_rig->subMeshGroundModelName = module_itor->get()->submeshes_ground_model_name;
1613  break;
1614  }
1615  }
1616 
1617  SetCurrentKeyword(RigDef::File::KEYWORD_INVALID);
1618 };
1619 
1620 void RigSpawner::ProcessSubmesh(RigDef::Submesh & def)
1621 {
1622  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1623 
1624  if (! CheckSubmeshLimit(1))
1625  {
1626  return;
1627  }
1628 
1629  m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_texcoord;
1630  m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_cab;
1631  m_rig->free_sub++;
1632  //initialize the next
1633  m_rig->subisback[m_rig->free_sub]=0;
1634 
1635  /* TEXCOORDS */
1636 
1637  std::vector<RigDef::Texcoord>::iterator texcoord_itor = def.texcoords.begin();
1638  for ( ; texcoord_itor != def.texcoords.end(); texcoord_itor++)
1639  {
1640  if (! CheckTexcoordLimit(1))
1641  {
1642  break;
1643  }
1644 
1645  m_rig->texcoords[m_rig->free_texcoord] = Ogre::Vector3(GetNodeIndexOrThrow(texcoord_itor->node), texcoord_itor->u, texcoord_itor->v);//(id, x, y);
1646  m_rig->free_texcoord++;
1647  }
1648 
1649  /* CAB */
1650 
1651  auto cab_itor = def.cab_triangles.begin();
1652  auto cab_itor_end = def.cab_triangles.end();
1653  for ( ; cab_itor != cab_itor_end; ++cab_itor)
1654  {
1655  if (! CheckCabLimit(1))
1656  {
1657  return;
1658  }
1659  else if (m_rig->free_collcab >= MAX_CABS)
1660  {
1661  std::stringstream msg;
1662  msg << "Collcab limit (" << MAX_CABS << ") exceeded";
1663  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
1664  return;
1665  }
1666 
1667  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3]=GetNodeIndexOrThrow(cab_itor->nodes[0]); //id1;
1668  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+1]=GetNodeIndexOrThrow(cab_itor->nodes[1]);//id2;
1669  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+2]=GetNodeIndexOrThrow(cab_itor->nodes[2]);//id3;
1670 
1671  //if (type=='c')
1672  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_c_CONTACT))
1673  {
1674  m_rig->collcabs[m_rig->free_collcab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1675  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=0;
1676  m_rig->free_collcab++;
1677  }
1678  //if (type=='p')
1679  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_p_10xTOUGHER))
1680  {
1681  m_rig->collcabs[m_rig->free_collcab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1682  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=1;
1683  m_rig->free_collcab++;
1684  }
1685  //if (type=='u')
1686  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_u_INVULNERABLE))
1687  {
1688  m_rig->collcabs[m_rig->free_collcab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1689  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=2;
1690  m_rig->free_collcab++;
1691  }
1692  //if (type=='b')
1693  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_b_BUOYANT))
1694  {
1695  m_rig->buoycabs[m_rig->free_buoycab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1696  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=0;
1697  m_rig->buoycabtypes[m_rig->free_buoycab]=Buoyance::BUOY_NORMAL;
1698  m_rig->free_buoycab++;
1699  if (m_rig->buoyance == nullptr)
1700  {
1701  m_rig->buoyance=new Buoyance();
1702  }
1703  }
1704  //if (type=='r')
1705  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_r_BUOYANT_ONLY_DRAG))
1706  {
1707  m_rig->buoycabs[m_rig->free_buoycab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1708  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=0;
1709  m_rig->buoycabtypes[m_rig->free_buoycab]=Buoyance::BUOY_DRAGONLY;
1710  m_rig->free_buoycab++;
1711  if (m_rig->buoyance == nullptr)
1712  {
1713  m_rig->buoyance=new Buoyance();
1714  }
1715  }
1716  //if (type=='s')
1717  if (BITMASK_IS_1(cab_itor->options, RigDef::Cab::OPTION_s_BUOYANT_NO_DRAG))
1718  {
1719  m_rig->buoycabs[m_rig->free_buoycab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1720  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=0;
1721  m_rig->buoycabtypes[m_rig->free_buoycab]=Buoyance::BUOY_DRAGLESS;
1722  m_rig->free_buoycab++;
1723  if (m_rig->buoyance == nullptr)
1724  {
1725  m_rig->buoyance=new Buoyance();
1726  }
1727  }
1728 
1729  int collcabs_type = -1;
1730  if (cab_itor->GetOption_D_ContactBuoyant())
1731  {
1732  collcabs_type = 0;
1733  }
1734  if (cab_itor->GetOption_F_10xTougherBuoyant())
1735  {
1736  collcabs_type = 1;
1737  }
1738  if (cab_itor->GetOption_S_UnpenetrableBuoyant())
1739  {
1740  collcabs_type = 2;
1741  }
1742 
1743  //if (type=='D' || type == 'F' || type == 'S')
1744  if (collcabs_type != -1)
1745  {
1746 
1747  if (m_rig->free_collcab >= MAX_CABS)
1748  {
1749  std::stringstream msg;
1750  msg << "Collcab limit (" << MAX_CABS << ") exceeded";
1751  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
1752  return;
1753  }
1754  else if (m_rig->free_buoycab >= MAX_CABS)
1755  {
1756  std::stringstream msg;
1757  msg << "Buoycab limit (" << MAX_CABS << ") exceeded";
1758  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
1759  return;
1760  }
1761 
1762  m_rig->collcabs[m_rig->free_collcab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1763  m_rig->collcabstype[m_rig->free_collcab]=collcabs_type;
1764  m_rig->free_collcab++;
1765  m_rig->buoycabs[m_rig->free_buoycab]=m_rig->free_cab;
1766  m_rig->buoycabtypes[m_rig->free_buoycab]=Buoyance::BUOY_NORMAL;
1767  m_rig->free_buoycab++;
1768  if (m_rig->buoyance == nullptr)
1769  {
1770  m_rig->buoyance=new Buoyance();
1771  }
1772  }
1773  m_rig->free_cab++;
1774  }
1775 
1776  /* BACKMESH */
1777 
1778  if (def.backmesh)
1779  {
1780 
1781  //close the current mesh
1782  m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_texcoord;
1783  m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_cab;
1784 
1785  // Check limit
1786  if (! CheckCabLimit(1))
1787  {
1788  return;
1789  }
1790 
1791  //make it normal
1792  m_rig->subisback[m_rig->free_sub]=0;
1793  m_rig->free_sub++;
1794 
1795  //add an extra front mesh
1796  int i;
1797  int start = (m_rig->free_sub==1) ? 0 : m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub-2];
1798  //texcoords
1799  for (i=start; i<m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub-1]; i++)
1800  {
1801  m_rig->texcoords[m_rig->free_texcoord] = m_rig->texcoords[i];;
1802  m_rig->free_texcoord++;
1803  }
1804  //cab
1805  start = (m_rig->free_sub==1) ? 0 : m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub-2];
1806 
1807  for (i=start; i<m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub-1]; i++)
1808  {
1809  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3]=m_rig->cabs[i*3];
1810  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+1]=m_rig->cabs[i*3+1];
1811  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+2]=m_rig->cabs[i*3+2];
1812  m_rig->free_cab++;
1813  }
1814  //finish it, this is a window
1815  m_rig->subisback[m_rig->free_sub]=2;
1816  //close the current mesh
1817  m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_texcoord;
1818  m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub]=m_rig->free_cab;
1819  //make is transparent
1820  m_rig->free_sub++;
1821 
1822 
1823  //add an extra back mesh
1824  //texcoords
1825  start = (m_rig->free_sub==1) ? 0 : m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub-2];
1826  for (i=start; i<m_rig->subtexcoords[m_rig->free_sub-1]; i++)
1827  {
1828  m_rig->texcoords[m_rig->free_texcoord]=m_rig->texcoords[i];;
1829  m_rig->free_texcoord++;
1830  }
1831 
1832  //cab
1833  start = (m_rig->free_sub==1) ? 0 : m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub-2];
1834  for (i=start; i<m_rig->subcabs[m_rig->free_sub-1]; i++)
1835  {
1836  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3]=m_rig->cabs[i*3+1];
1837  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+1]=m_rig->cabs[i*3];
1838  m_rig->cabs[m_rig->free_cab*3+2]=m_rig->cabs[i*3+2];
1839  m_rig->free_cab++;
1840  }
1841 
1842  m_rig->subisback[m_rig->free_sub]=1;
1843  }
1844 }
1845 
1846 void RigSpawner::ProcessFlexbody(boost::shared_ptr<RigDef::Flexbody> def)
1847 {
1848  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1849 
1850  if (! CheckFlexbodyLimit(1))
1851  {
1852  return;
1853  }
1854 
1855  char unique_name[200];
1856  sprintf(unique_name, "Flexbody-%s-%d", m_rig->truckname, m_rig->free_flexbody);
1857 
1858  Ogre::Quaternion rot=Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def->rotation.z), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_Z);
1859  rot=rot*Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def->rotation.y), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_Y);
1860  rot=rot*Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def->rotation.x), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_X);
1861 
1862  /* Collect nodes */
1863  std::vector<unsigned int> node_indices;
1864  node_indices.reserve(def->node_list.size());
1865  bool nodes_found = true;
1866  auto node_itor = def->node_list.begin();
1867  auto node_end = def->node_list.end();
1868  for (; node_itor != node_end; ++node_itor)
1869  {
1870  auto result = this->GetNodeIndex(*node_itor);
1871  if (!result.second)
1872  {
1873  nodes_found = false;
1874  break;
1875  }
1876  node_indices.push_back(result.first);
1877  }
1878 
1879  if (! nodes_found)
1880  {
1881  std::stringstream msg;
1882  msg << "Failed to collect nodes from node-ranges, skipping flexbody '" << def->mesh_name << "'";
1883  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
1884  return;
1885  }
1886 
1887  int reference_node = FindNodeIndex(def->reference_node);
1888  int x_axis_node = FindNodeIndex(def->x_axis_node);
1889  int y_axis_node = FindNodeIndex(def->y_axis_node);
1890  if (reference_node == -1 || x_axis_node == -1 || y_axis_node == -1)
1891  {
1892  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Failed to find required nodes, skipping flexbody '" + def->mesh_name + "'");
1893  }
1894 
1895  auto * flexbody = m_flex_factory.CreateFlexBody(
1896  m_rig->free_node,
1897  def->mesh_name.c_str(),
1898  unique_name,
1899  reference_node,
1900  x_axis_node,
1901  y_axis_node,
1902  def->offset,
1903  rot,
1904  node_indices
1905  );
1906  int camera_mode = (def->camera_settings.mode == RigDef::CameraSettings::MODE_CINECAM)
1907  ? (int)def->camera_settings.cinecam_index
1908  : (int)def->camera_settings.mode;
1909  flexbody->setCameraMode(camera_mode);
1910 
1911  m_rig->flexbodies[m_rig->free_flexbody] = flexbody;
1912  m_rig->free_flexbody++;
1913 }
1914 
1915 void RigSpawner::ProcessProp(RigDef::Prop & def)
1916 {
1917  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
1918 
1919  if (! CheckPropLimit(1))
1920  {
1921  return;
1922  }
1923 
1924  prop_t & prop = m_rig->props[m_rig->free_prop];
1925  m_rig->free_prop++;
1926  memset(&prop, 0, sizeof(prop_t)); /* Initialize prop memory to avoid invalid pointers. */
1927 
1928  prop.noderef = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.reference_node);
1929  prop.nodex = FindNodeIndex(def.x_axis_node);
1930  prop.nodey = FindNodeIndex(def.y_axis_node);
1931  if (prop.nodex == -1 || prop.nodey == -1)
1932  {
1933  return;
1934  }
1935  prop.offsetx = def.offset.x;
1936  prop.offsety = def.offset.y;
1937  prop.offsetz = def.offset.z;
1938  prop.orgoffsetX = def.offset.x;
1939  prop.orgoffsetY = def.offset.y;
1940  prop.orgoffsetZ = def.offset.z;
1941  prop.rotaX = def.rotation.x;
1942  prop.rotaY = def.rotation.y;
1943  prop.rotaZ = def.rotation.z;
1944  prop.rot = Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def.rotation.z), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_Z);
1945  prop.rot = prop.rot * Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def.rotation.y), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_Y);
1946  prop.rot = prop.rot * Ogre::Quaternion(Ogre::Degree(def.rotation.x), Ogre::Vector3::UNIT_X);
1947  prop.cameramode = def.camera_settings.mode; /* Handles default value */
1948  prop.wheelrotdegree = 160.f;
1949  /* Set no animation by default */
1950  prop.animKey[0] = -1;
1951  prop.animKeyState[0] = -1.f;
1952 
1953  /* SPECIAL PROPS */
1954 
1955  /* Rear view mirror (left) */
1956  if (def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_LEFT_REAR_VIEW_MIRROR)
1957  {
1958  prop.mirror = 1;
1959  }
1960 
1961  /* Rear view mirror (right) */
1962  if (def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_RIGHT_REAR_VIEW_MIRROR)
1963  {
1964  prop.mirror = -1;
1965  }
1966 
1967  /* Custom steering wheel */
1968  Ogre::Vector3 steering_wheel_offset = Ogre::Vector3::ZERO;
1969  if (def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_STEERING_WHEEL_LEFT_HANDED)
1970  {
1971  steering_wheel_offset = Ogre::Vector3(-0.67, -0.61,0.24);
1972  }
1973  if (def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_STEERING_WHEEL_RIGHT_HANDED)
1974  {
1975  steering_wheel_offset = Ogre::Vector3(0.67, -0.61,0.24);
1976  }
1977  if (steering_wheel_offset != Ogre::Vector3::ZERO)
1978  {
1979  if (def.special_prop_steering_wheel._offset_is_set)
1980  {
1981  steering_wheel_offset = def.special_prop_steering_wheel.offset;
1982  }
1983  prop.wheelrotdegree = def.special_prop_steering_wheel.rotation_angle;
1984  prop.wheel = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
1985  prop.wheelpos = steering_wheel_offset;
1986  MeshObject *mesh_object = new MeshObject(
1987  def.special_prop_steering_wheel.mesh_name,
1988  "",
1989  prop.wheel,
1990  m_rig->usedSkin,
1991  m_enable_background_loading
1992  );
1993  mesh_object->setSimpleMaterialColour(Ogre::ColourValue(0, 0.5, 0.5));
1994  mesh_object->setMaterialFunctionMapper(m_rig->materialFunctionMapper, m_rig->materialReplacer);
1995  }
1996 
1997  /* CREATE THE PROP */
1998 
1999  prop.snode = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
2000  prop.mo = new MeshObject(def.mesh_name, "", prop.snode, m_rig->usedSkin, m_enable_background_loading);
2001  prop.mo->setSimpleMaterialColour(Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 0));
2002  prop.mo->setMaterialFunctionMapper(m_rig->materialFunctionMapper, m_rig->materialReplacer);
2003  prop.mo->setCastShadows(true); // Orig code {{ prop.mo->setCastShadows(shadowmode != 0); }}, shadowmode has default value 1 and changes with undocumented directive 'set_shadows'
2004  prop.beacontype = 'n'; // Orig: hardcoded in BTS_PROPS
2005 
2006  if (def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_SPINPROP)
2007  {
2008  prop.spinner = 1;
2009  prop.mo->setCastShadows(false);
2010  prop.snode->setVisible(false);
2011  }
2012  else if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_PALE)
2013  {
2014  prop.pale = 1;
2015  }
2016  else if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_DRIVER_SEAT)
2017  {
2018  m_rig->driversseatfound = true;
2019  m_rig->driverSeat = & prop;
2020  prop.mo->setMaterialName("driversseat");
2021  }
2022  else if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_SPINPROP)
2023  {
2024  m_rig->driversseatfound = true;
2025  m_rig->driverSeat = & prop;
2026  }
2027  else if (m_rig->flaresMode > 0)
2028  {
2029  if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_BEACON)
2030  {
2031  prop.beacontype = 'b';
2032  prop.bpos[0] = 2.0 * 3.14 * (std::rand() / RAND_MAX);
2033  prop.brate[0] = 4.0 * 3.14 + (std::rand() / RAND_MAX) - 0.5;
2034  /* the light */
2035  prop.light[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->createLight();
2036  prop.light[0]->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_SPOTLIGHT);
2037  prop.light[0]->setDiffuseColour(def.special_prop_beacon.color);
2038  prop.light[0]->setSpecularColour(def.special_prop_beacon.color);
2039  prop.light[0]->setAttenuation(50.0, 1.0, 0.3, 0.0);
2040  prop.light[0]->setSpotlightRange( Ogre::Degree(35), Ogre::Degree(45) );
2041  prop.light[0]->setCastShadows(false);
2042  prop.light[0]->setVisible(false);
2043  /* the flare billboard */
2044  prop.bbsnode[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
2045  prop.bbs[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(1); //(propname,1);
2046  prop.bbs[0]->createBillboard(0,0,0);
2047  if (prop.bbs[0])
2048  {
2049  prop.bbs[0]->setMaterialName(def.special_prop_beacon.flare_material_name);
2050  prop.bbs[0]->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
2051  }
2052  prop.bbs[0]->setVisible(false);
2053  prop.bbsnode[0]->setVisible(false);
2054  }
2055  else if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_REDBEACON)
2056  {
2057  prop.brate[0] = 1.0;
2058  prop.beacontype = 'r';
2059  //the light
2060  prop.light[0]=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight();//propname);
2061  prop.light[0]->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_POINT);
2062  prop.light[0]->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0.0, 0.0));
2063  prop.light[0]->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0.0, 0.0));
2064  prop.light[0]->setAttenuation(50.0, 1.0, 0.3, 0.0);
2065  prop.light[0]->setCastShadows(false);
2066  prop.light[0]->setVisible(false);
2067  //the flare billboard
2068  prop.bbsnode[0] = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
2069  prop.bbs[0]=gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(1); //propname,1);
2070  prop.bbs[0]->createBillboard(0,0,0);
2071  if (prop.bbs[0])
2072  {
2073  prop.bbs[0]->setMaterialName("tracks/redbeaconflare");
2074  prop.bbs[0]->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
2075  }
2076  if (prop.bbs[0])
2077  {
2078  prop.bbsnode[0]->attachObject(prop.bbs[0]);
2079  }
2080  prop.bbsnode[0]->setVisible(false);
2081  prop.bbs[0]->setDefaultDimensions(1.0, 1.0);
2082  }
2083  else if(def.special == RigDef::Prop::SPECIAL_LIGHTBAR)
2084  {
2085  int k;
2086  m_rig->ispolice = true;
2087  prop.beacontype='p';
2088  for (k=0; k<4; k++)
2089  {
2090  prop.bpos[k]=2.0*3.14*(std::rand()/RAND_MAX);
2091  prop.brate[k]=4.0*3.14+(std::rand()/RAND_MAX)-0.5;
2092  prop.bbs[k]=0;
2093  //the light
2094  //char rpname[256];
2095  //sprintf(rpname,"%s-%i", propname, k);
2096  prop.light[k]=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(); //rpname);
2097  prop.light[k]->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_SPOTLIGHT);
2098  if (k>1)
2099  {
2100  prop.light[k]->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0.0, 0.0));
2101  prop.light[k]->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0.0, 0.0));
2102  }
2103  else
2104  {
2105  prop.light[k]->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(0.0, 0.5, 1.0));
2106  prop.light[k]->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(0.0, 0.5, 1.0));
2107  }
2108  prop.light[k]->setAttenuation(50.0, 1.0, 0.3, 0.0);
2109  prop.light[k]->setSpotlightRange( Ogre::Degree(35), Ogre::Degree(45) );
2110  prop.light[k]->setCastShadows(false);
2111  prop.light[k]->setVisible(false);
2112  //the flare billboard
2113  prop.bbsnode[k] = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
2114  prop.bbs[k]=gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(1); //rpname,1);
2115  prop.bbs[k]->createBillboard(0,0,0);
2116  if (prop.bbs[k])
2117  {
2118  if (k>1)
2119  {
2120  prop.bbs[k]->setMaterialName("tracks/brightredflare");
2121  }
2122  else
2123  {
2124  prop.bbs[k]->setMaterialName("tracks/brightblueflare");
2125  }
2126 
2127  if (prop.bbs[k])
2128  {
2129  prop.bbs[k]->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
2130  prop.bbsnode[k]->attachObject(prop.bbs[k]);
2131  }
2132  }
2133  prop.bbsnode[k]->setVisible(false);
2134  }
2135  }
2136  }
2137 
2138  /* PROCESS ANIMATIONS */
2139 
2140  if (def.animations.size() > 10)
2141  {
2142  std::stringstream msg;
2143  msg << "Prop (mesh: " << def.mesh_name << ") has too many animations: " << def.animations.size() << " (max. is 10). Using first 10 ...";
2144  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2145  }
2146 
2147  std::list<RigDef::Animation>::iterator anim_itor = def.animations.begin();
2148  int anim_index = 0;
2149  while (anim_itor != def.animations.end() && anim_index < 10)
2150  {
2151  prop.animKeyState[anim_index] = -1.0f; // Orig: hardcoded in {add_animation}
2152 
2153  /* Arg #1: ratio */
2154  prop.animratio[anim_index] = anim_itor->ratio;
2155  if (anim_itor->ratio == 0)
2156  {
2157  std::stringstream msg;
2158  msg << "Prop (mesh: " << def.mesh_name << ") has invalid animation ratio (0), using it anyway (compatibility)...";
2159  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2160  }
2161 
2162  /* Arg #2: option1 (lower limit) */
2163  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit; /* Handles default */
2164 
2165  /* Arg #3: option2 (upper limit) */
2166  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit; /* Handles default */
2167 
2168  /* Arg #4: source */
2169  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::SOURCE_AIRSPEED)) { /* (NOTE: code formatting relaxed) */
2170  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animFlags[anim_index], ANIM_FLAG_AIRSPEED);
2171  }

2256  }
2257  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::SOURCE_AIR_RUDDER)) {

2259  }
2260  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::SOURCE_BOAT_RUDDER)) {

2262  }

2271  }

2279  }

2282  prop.animOpt3[anim_index] = static_cast<float>(source_itor->motor);
2283  }
2284  if (BITMASK_IS_1(source_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::MotorSource::SOURCE_AERO_TORQUE)) {
2285  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animFlags[anim_index], ANIM_FLAG_AETORQUE);
2286  prop.animOpt3[anim_index] = static_cast<float>(source_itor->motor);
2287  }
2288  if (BITMASK_IS_1(source_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::MotorSource::SOURCE_AERO_PITCH)) {
2289  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animFlags[anim_index], ANIM_FLAG_AEPITCH);
2290  prop.animOpt3[anim_index] = static_cast<float>(source_itor->motor);
2291  }
2292  if (BITMASK_IS_1(source_itor->source, RigDef::Animation::MotorSource::SOURCE_AERO_STATUS)) {
2293  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animFlags[anim_index], ANIM_FLAG_AESTATUS);
2294  prop.animOpt3[anim_index] = static_cast<float>(source_itor->motor);
2295  }
2296  }
2297  if (prop.animFlags[anim_index] == 0)
2298  {
2299  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Failed to identify animation source");
2300  }
2301 
2302  /* Anim modes */
2303  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_X)) {
2304  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_ROTA_X);
2305  }
2306  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_Y)) {
2307  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_ROTA_Y);
2308  }
2309  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_Z)) {
2310  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_ROTA_Z);
2311  }
2312  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_X)) {
2313  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_OFFSET_X);
2314  }
2315  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_Y)) {
2316  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_OFFSET_Y);
2317  }
2318  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_Z)) {
2319  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_OFFSET_Z);
2320  }
2321  if (prop.animMode[anim_index] == 0)
2322  {
2323  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Failed to identify animation mode");
2324  }
2325 
2326  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_AUTO_ANIMATE))
2327  {
2328  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_AUTOANIMATE);
2329 
2330  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_X)) {
2331  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.rotaX;
2332  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.rotaX;
2333  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.rotaX;
2334  }
2335  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_Y)) {
2336  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.rotaY;
2337  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.rotaY;
2338  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.rotaY;
2339  }
2340  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_ROTATION_Z)) {
2341  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.rotaZ;
2342  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.rotaZ;
2343  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.rotaZ;
2344  }
2345  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_X)) {
2346  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.orgoffsetX;
2347  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.orgoffsetX;
2348  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.orgoffsetX;
2349  }
2350  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_Y)) {
2351  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.orgoffsetY;
2352  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.orgoffsetY;
2353  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.orgoffsetY;
2354  }
2355  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_OFFSET_Z)) {
2356  prop.animOpt1[anim_index] = anim_itor->lower_limit + prop.orgoffsetZ;
2357  prop.animOpt2[anim_index] = anim_itor->upper_limit + prop.orgoffsetZ;
2358  prop.animOpt4[anim_index] = prop.orgoffsetZ;
2359  }
2360  }
2361  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_NO_FLIP))
2362  {
2363  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_NOFLIP);
2364  }
2365  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_BOUNCE))
2366  {
2367  BITMASK_SET_1(prop.animMode[anim_index], ANIM_MODE_BOUNCE);
2368  prop.animOpt5[anim_index] = 1.f;
2369  }
2370  if (BITMASK_IS_1(anim_itor->mode, RigDef::Animation::MODE_EVENT_LOCK))
2371  {
2372  prop.animKeyState[anim_index] = 0.0f;
2373  prop.lastanimKS[anim_index] = 0.0f;
2374  }
2375 
2376  /* Parameter 'event:' */
2377 
2378  if (! anim_itor->event.empty())
2379  {
2380  // we are using keys as source
2381  prop.animFlags[anim_index] |= ANIM_FLAG_EVENT;
2382 
2383  int event_id = RoR::Application::GetInputEngine()->resolveEventName(anim_itor->event);
2384  if (event_id == -1)
2385  {
2386  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "Unknown animation event: " + anim_itor->event);
2387  }
2388  else
2389  {
2390  prop.animKey[anim_index] = event_id;
2391  }
2392  }
2393 
2394  /* Advance */
2395  anim_itor++;
2396  anim_index++;
2397  }
2398 }

2400 void RigSpawner::ProcessMaterialFlareBinding(RigDef::MaterialFlareBinding & def)
2401 {
2402  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
2403 
2404  std::stringstream mat_clone_name;
2405  mat_clone_name << def.material_name << "_mfb_" << m_rig->truckname;
2406  Ogre::MaterialPtr material = CloneMaterial(def.material_name, mat_clone_name.str());
2407  if (material.isNull())
2408  {
2409  return;
2410  }
2411 
2412  if (m_rig->materialFunctionMapper != nullptr)
2413  {
2414  MaterialFunctionMapper::materialmapping_t mapping;
2415  mapping.originalmaterial = def.material_name;
2416  mapping.material = mat_clone_name.str();
2417  mapping.type = 0; // Orig: hardcoded in BTS_MATERIALFLAREBINDINGS
2418 
2419  m_rig->materialFunctionMapper->addMaterial(def.flare_number, mapping);
2420  }
2421 }
2422 
2423 void RigSpawner::ProcessFlare2(RigDef::Flare2 & def)
2424 {
2425  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
2426 
2427  if (m_rig->flaresMode == 0)
2428  {
2429  return;
2430  }
2431 
2432  int blink_delay = def.blink_delay_milis;
2433  float size = def.size;
2434 
2435  /* Backwards compatibility */
2436  if (blink_delay == -2)
2437  {
2438  if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_l_LEFT_BLINKER || def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_l_LEFT_BLINKER)
2439  {
2440  blink_delay = -1; /* Default blink */
2441  }
2442  else
2443  {
2444  blink_delay = 0; /* Default no blink */
2445  }
2446  }
2447 
2448  if (size == -2.f && def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_f_HEADLIGHT)
2449  {
2450  size = 1.f;
2451  }
2452  else if ((size == -2.f && def.type != RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_f_HEADLIGHT) || size == -1.f)
2453  {
2454  size = 0.5f;
2455  }
2456 
2457  flare_t flare;
2458  flare.type = def.type;
2459  flare.controlnumber = def.control_number;
2460  flare.controltoggle_status = false;
2461  flare.blinkdelay = (blink_delay == -1) ? 0.5f : blink_delay / 1000.f;
2462  flare.blinkdelay_curr = 0.f;
2463  flare.blinkdelay_state = false;
2464  flare.noderef = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.reference_node);
2465  flare.nodex = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.node_axis_x);
2466  flare.nodey = GetNodeIndexOrThrow(def.node_axis_y);
2467  flare.offsetx = def.offset.x;
2468  flare.offsety = def.offset.y;
2469  flare.offsetz = def.offset.z;
2470  flare.size = size;
2471 
2472  /* Visuals */
2473  flare.snode = gEnv->sceneManager->getRootSceneNode()->createChildSceneNode();
2474  std::stringstream flare_name;
2475  flare_name << "flare-" << m_rig->truckname << "-" << m_rig->free_flare;
2476  flare.bbs = gEnv->sceneManager->createBillboardSet(flare_name.str(), 1);
2477  bool using_default_material = true;
2478  if (flare.bbs == nullptr)
2479  {
2480  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Failed to create flare: '" + flare_name.str() + "', continuing without it (compatibility)...");
2481  }
2482  else
2483  {
2484  flare.bbs->createBillboard(0,0,0);
2485  flare.bbs->setVisibilityFlags(DEPTHMAP_DISABLED);
2486 
2487  if (def.material_name.length() == 0 || def.material_name == "default")
2488  {
2489  if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_b_BRAKELIGHT)
2490  {
2491  flare.bbs->setMaterialName("tracks/brakeflare");
2492  }
2493  else if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_l_LEFT_BLINKER || (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_r_RIGHT_BLINKER))
2494  {
2495  flare.bbs->setMaterialName("tracks/blinkflare");
2496  }
2497  else
2498  {
2499  flare.bbs->setMaterialName("tracks/flare");
2500  }
2501  }
2502  else
2503  {
2504  using_default_material = false;
2505  flare.bbs->setMaterialName(def.material_name);
2506  }
2507  flare.snode->attachObject(flare.bbs);
2508  }
2509  flare.isVisible = true;
2510  flare.light = nullptr;
2511 
2512  if (m_rig->flaresMode >= 2 && size > 0.001)
2513  {
2514  //if (type == 'f' && usingDefaultMaterial && flaresMode >=2 && size > 0.001)
2515  if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_f_HEADLIGHT && using_default_material )
2516  {
2517  /* front light */
2518  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2519  flare.light->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_SPOTLIGHT);
2520  flare.light->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2521  flare.light->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2522  flare.light->setAttenuation(400, 0.9, 0, 0);
2523  flare.light->setSpotlightRange( Ogre::Degree(35), Ogre::Degree(45) );
2524  flare.light->setCastShadows(false);
2525  }
2526  }
2527  if (m_rig->flaresMode >= 4 && size > 0.001)
2528  {
2529  //else if (type == 'f' && !usingDefaultMaterial && flaresMode >=4 && size > 0.001)
2530  if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_f_HEADLIGHT && ! using_default_material)
2531  {
2532  /* this is a quick fix for the red backlight when frontlight is switched on */
2533  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2534  flare.light->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0, 0));
2535  flare.light->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0, 0));
2536  flare.light->setAttenuation(10.0, 1.0, 0, 0);
2537  }
2538  //else if (type == 'R' && flaresMode >= 4 && size > 0.001)
2539  else if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_R_REVERSE_LIGHT)
2540  {
2541  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2542  flare.light->setDiffuseColour(Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2543  flare.light->setSpecularColour(Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2544  flare.light->setAttenuation(20.0, 1, 0, 0);
2545  }
2546  //else if (type == 'b' && flaresMode >= 4 && size > 0.001)
2547  else if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_b_BRAKELIGHT)
2548  {
2549  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2550  flare.light->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0, 0));
2551  flare.light->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1.0, 0, 0));
2552  flare.light->setAttenuation(10.0, 1.0, 0, 0);
2553  }
2554  //else if ((type == 'l' || type == 'r') && flaresMode >= 4 && size > 0.001)
2555  else if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_l_LEFT_BLINKER || (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_r_RIGHT_BLINKER))
2556  {
2557  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2558  flare.light->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 0));
2559  flare.light->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 0));
2560  flare.light->setAttenuation(10.0, 1, 1, 0);
2561  }
2562  //else if ((type == 'u') && flaresMode >= 4 && size > 0.001)
2563  else if (def.type == RigDef::Flare2::TYPE_u_USER)
2564  {
2565  /* user light always white (TODO: improve this) */
2566  flare.light=gEnv->sceneManager->createLight(flare_name.str());
2567  flare.light->setDiffuseColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2568  flare.light->setSpecularColour( Ogre::ColourValue(1, 1, 1));
2569  flare.light->setAttenuation(50.0, 1.0, 1, 0.2);
2570 
2571  if (m_rig->netCustomLightArray_counter < 4)
2572  {
2573  m_rig->netCustomLightArray[m_rig->netCustomLightArray_counter] = m_rig->free_flare;
2574  m_rig->netCustomLightArray_counter++;
2575  }
2576  }
2577  }
2578 
2579  /* Finalize light */
2580  if (flare.light != nullptr)
2581  {
2582  flare.light->setType(Ogre::Light::LT_SPOTLIGHT);
2583  flare.light->setSpotlightRange( Ogre::Degree(35), Ogre::Degree(45) );
2584  flare.light->setCastShadows(false);
2585  }
2586  m_rig->flares.push_back(flare);
2587  m_rig->free_flare++;
2588 }

2590 Ogre::MaterialPtr RigSpawner::CloneMaterial(Ogre::String const & source_name, Ogre::String const & clone_name)
2591 {
2592  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
2593 
2594  Ogre::MaterialPtr src_mat = static_cast<Ogre::MaterialPtr>(Ogre::MaterialManager::getSingleton().getByName(source_name));
2595  if (src_mat.isNull())
2596  {
2597  std::stringstream msg;
2598  msg << "Built-in material '" << source_name << "' missing! Skipping...";
2599  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
2600  return Ogre::MaterialPtr();
2601  }
2602  return src_mat->clone(clone_name);
2603 }
2604 
2605 void RigSpawner::ProcessManagedMaterial(RigDef::ManagedMaterial & def)
2606 {
2607  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
2608 
2609  Ogre::MaterialPtr test = static_cast<Ogre::MaterialPtr>(Ogre::MaterialManager::getSingleton().getByName(def.name));
2610  if (!test.isNull())
2611  {
2612  std::stringstream msg;
2613  msg << "Managed material '" << def.name << "' already exists (probably because the vehicle was already spawned before)";
2614  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2615  }
2616 
2617  Ogre::MaterialPtr material;
2618  if (def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_FLEXMESH_STANDARD || def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_FLEXMESH_TRANSPARENT)
2619  {
2620  Ogre::String mat_name_base
2621  = (def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_FLEXMESH_STANDARD)
2622  ? "managed/flexmesh_standard"
2623  : "managed/flexmesh_transparent";
2624 
2625  if (def.HasDamagedDiffuseMap())
2626  {
2627  if (def.HasSpecularMap())
2628  {
2629  /* FLEXMESH, damage, specular */
2630  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/speculardamage", def.name);
2631  if (material.isNull())
2632  {
2633  return;
2634  }
2635  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.diffuse_map);
2636  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Dmg_Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.damaged_diffuse_map);
2637  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("SpecularMapping1")->getTextureUnitState("SpecularMapping1_Tex")->setTextureName(def.specular_map);
2638  }
2639  else
2640  {
2641  /* FLEXMESH, damage, no_specular */
2642  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/damageonly", def.name);
2643  if (material.isNull())
2644  {
2645  return;
2646  }
2647  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.diffuse_map);
2648  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Dmg_Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.damaged_diffuse_map);
2649  }
2650  if (def.options.double_sided)
2651  {
2652  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->setCullingMode(Ogre::CULL_NONE);
2653  if (def.HasSpecularMap())
2654  {
2655  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("SpecularMapping1")->setCullingMode(Ogre::CULL_NONE);
2656  }
2657  }
2658  }
2659  else
2660  {
2661  if (def.HasSpecularMap())
2662  {
2663  /* FLEXMESH, no_damage, specular */
2664  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/specularonly", def.name);
2665  if (material.isNull())
2666  {
2667  return;
2668  }
2669  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.diffuse_map);
2670  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("SpecularMapping1")->getTextureUnitState("SpecularMapping1_Tex")->setTextureName(def.specular_map);
2671  }
2672  else
2673  {
2674  /* FLEXMESH, no_damage, no_specular */
2675  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/simple", def.name);
2676  if (material.isNull())
2677  {
2678  return;
2679  }
2680  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.diffuse_map);
2681  }
2682  if (def.options.double_sided)
2683  {
2684  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->setCullingMode(Ogre::CULL_NONE);
2685  if (def.HasSpecularMap())
2686  {
2687  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("SpecularMapping1")->setCullingMode(Ogre::CULL_NONE);
2688  }
2689  }
2690  }
2691  }
2692  else if (def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_STANDARD || def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_TRANSPARENT)
2693  {
2694  Ogre::String mat_name_base
2695  = (def.type == RigDef::ManagedMaterial::TYPE_MESH_STANDARD)
2696  ? "managed/mesh_standard"
2697  : "managed/mesh_transparent";
2698 
2699  if (def.HasSpecularMap())
2700  {
2701  /* MESH, specular */
2702  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/specular", def.name);
2703  if (material.isNull())
2704  {
2705  return;
2706  }
2707  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("BaseRender")->getTextureUnitState("Diffuse_Map")->setTextureName(def.diffuse_map);
2708  material->getTechnique("BaseTechnique")->getPass("SpecularMapping1")->getTextureUnitState("SpecularMapping1_Tex")->setTextureName(def.specular_map);
2709  }
2710  else
2711  {
2712  /* MESH, no_specular */
2713  material = CloneMaterial(mat_name_base + "/simple", def.name);
2714  if (material.isNull())
2715  {

2757 bool RigSpawner::AssignWheelToAxle(int & _out_axle_wheel, node_t *axis_node_1, node_t *axis_node_2)
2758 {

2762  {

2765  || (wheel.refnode0 == axis_node_2 && wheel.refnode1 == axis_node_1)

2775 void RigSpawner::ProcessAxle(RigDef::Axle & def)
2776 {
2777  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
2778 
2779  if (! CheckAxleLimit(1))
2780  {
2781  return;
2782  }
2783 
2784  node_t *wheel_1_node_1 = GetNodePointerOrThrow(def.wheels[0][0]);
2785  node_t *wheel_1_node_2 = GetNodePointerOrThrow(def.wheels[0][1]);
2786  node_t *wheel_2_node_1 = GetNodePointerOrThrow(def.wheels[1][0]);
2787  node_t *wheel_2_node_2 = GetNodePointerOrThrow(def.wheels[1][1]);
2788  Axle *axle = new Axle();
2789 
2790  if (! AssignWheelToAxle(axle->wheel_1, wheel_1_node_1, wheel_1_node_2))
2791  {
2792  std::stringstream msg;
2793  msg << "Couldn't find wheel with axis nodes '" << def.wheels[0][0].ToString()
2794  << "' and '" << def.wheels[0][1].ToString() << "'";
2795  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2796  }
2797 
2798  if (! AssignWheelToAxle(axle->wheel_2, wheel_2_node_1, wheel_2_node_2))
2799  {
2800  std::stringstream msg;
2801  msg << "Couldn't find wheel with axis nodes '" << def.wheels[1][0].ToString()
2802  << "' and '" << def.wheels[1][1].ToString() << "'";
2803  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, msg.str());
2804  }
2805 
2806  if (def.options.size() == 0)
2807  {
2808  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_INFO, "No differential defined, defaulting to Open & Locked");
2809  axle->addDiffType(OPEN_DIFF);
2810  axle->addDiffType(LOCKED_DIFF);
2811  }
2812  else
2813  {
2814  auto end = def.options.end();
2815  for (auto itor = def.options.begin(); itor != end; ++itor)
2816  {
2817  switch (*itor)
2818  {
2819  case RigDef::Axle::OPTION_l_LOCKED:
2820  axle->addDiffType(LOCKED_DIFF);
2821  break;
2822  case RigDef::Axle::OPTION_o_OPEN:
2823  axle->addDiffType(OPEN_DIFF);
2824  break;
2825  case RigDef::Axle::OPTION_s_SPLIT:
2826  axle->addDiffType(SPLIT_DIFF);
2827  break;
2828  default:
2829  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_WARNING, "Unknown differential type: " + *itor);
2830  break;
2831  }
2832  }
2833  }
2834 
2835  m_rig->axles[m_rig->free_axle] = axle;
2836  m_rig->free_axle++;
2837 }

2948 void RigSpawner::ProcessTie(RigDef::Tie & def)
2949 {

2954  return;

2964  beam.d = def.beam_defaults->GetScaledDamping();

2966  beam.L = def.max_reach_length;
2967  beam.refL = def.max_reach_length;
2968  beam.Lhydro = def.max_reach_length;
2969  beam.bounded = ROPE;
2970  beam.disabled = true;
2971  beam.commandRatioLong = def.auto_shorten_rate;
2972  beam.commandRatioShort = def.auto_shorten_rate;
2973  beam.commandShort = def.min_length;
2974  beam.commandLong = def.max_length;
2975  beam.maxtiestress = def.max_stress;
2976  beam.diameter = DEFAULT_BEAM_DIAMETER;
2977  CreateBeamVisuals(beam, beam_index, def.beam_defaults, false);
2978 
2979  /* Register tie */
2980  tie_t tie;
2981  tie.group = def.group;
2982  tie.tying = false;
2983  tie.tied = false;
2984  tie.beam = & beam;

3035 void RigSpawner::ProcessSlidenode(RigDef::SlideNode & def)
3036 {
3037  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3038 
3039  node_t & node = GetNodeOrThrow(def.slide_node);
3040  SlideNode slide_node(& node, nullptr);
3041  slide_node.setThreshold(def.tolerance);
3042  slide_node.setSpringRate(def.spring_rate);
3043  slide_node.setAttachmentRate(def.spring_rate);
3044  if (def._break_force_set)
3045  {
3046  slide_node.setBreakForce(def.break_force);
3047  }
3048  slide_node.setAttachmentDistance(def.max_attachment_distance);
3049 
3050  /* Constraints */
3051  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.constraint_flags, RigDef::SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_ALL))
3052  {
3053  slide_node.setAttachRule( ATTACH_ALL );
3054  }
3055  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.constraint_flags, RigDef::SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_SELF))
3056  {
3057  slide_node.setAttachRule( ATTACH_SELF );
3058  }
3059  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.constraint_flags, RigDef::SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_FOREIGN))
3060  {
3061  slide_node.setAttachRule( ATTACH_FOREIGN );
3062  }
3063  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.constraint_flags, RigDef::SlideNode::CONSTRAINT_ATTACH_NONE))
3064  {
3065  slide_node.setAttachRule( ATTACH_NONE );
3066  }
3067 
3068  /* RailGroup */
3069  RailGroup *rail_group = nullptr;
3070  if (def._railgroup_id_set)
3071  {
3072  std::vector<RailGroup*>::iterator itor = m_rig->mRailGroups.begin();
3073  for ( ; itor != m_rig->mRailGroups.end(); itor++)
3074  {
3075  if ((*itor)->getID() == def.railgroup_id)
3076  {
3077  rail_group = *itor;
3078  break;
3079  }
3080  }
3081 
3082  if (rail_group == nullptr)
3083  {
3084  std::stringstream msg;
3085  msg << "Specified rail group id '" << def.railgroup_id << "' not found. Ignoring slidenode...";
3086  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3087  return;
3088  }
3089  }
3090  else if (def.rail_node_ranges.size() > 0)
3091  {
3092  Rail *rail = CreateRail(def.rail_node_ranges);
3093  if (rail == nullptr)
3094  {
3095  return;
3096  }
3097  rail_group = new RailGroup(rail);
3098  m_rig->mRailGroups.push_back(rail_group);
3099  }
3100  else
3101  {
3102  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, "No RailGroup available for SlideNode, skipping...");
3103  }
3104 
3105  slide_node.setDefaultRail(rail_group);
3106  m_rig->mSlideNodes.push_back(slide_node);
3107 }

3109 int RigSpawner::FindNodeIndex(RigDef::Node::Ref & node_ref, bool silent /* Default: false */)
3110 {
3111  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3112 
3113  std::pair<unsigned int, bool> result = GetNodeIndex(node_ref, /* quiet */ true);
3114  if (result.second)
3115  {
3116  return static_cast<int>(result.first);
3117  }
3118  else
3119  {
3120  if (! silent)
3121  {
3122  std::stringstream msg;
3123  msg << "Failed to find node by reference: " << node_ref.ToString();
3124  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3125  }
3126  return -1; /* Node not found */
3127  }

3129 
3130 bool RigSpawner::CollectNodesFromRanges(
3131  std::vector<RigDef::Node::Range> & node_ranges,
3132  std::vector<unsigned int> & out_node_indices
3133  )
3134 {
3135  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3136 
3137  std::vector<RigDef::Node::Range>::iterator itor = node_ranges.begin();
3138  for ( ; itor != node_ranges.end(); itor++)
3139  {
3140  if (itor->IsRange())
3141  {
3142 
3143  int result_a = FindNodeIndex(itor->start, /* silent */ false);
3144  int result_b = FindNodeIndex(itor->end, /* silent */ true);
3145 
3146  unsigned int start = 0;
3147  unsigned int end = 0;
3148 
3149  if (result_a == -1)
3150  {
3151  return false;
3152  }
3153  else
3154  {
3155  start = static_cast<unsigned int>(result_a);
3156  }
3157 
3158  if (result_b == -1)
3159  {
3160  std::stringstream msg;
3161  msg << "Encountered non-existent node '" << itor->end.ToString() << "' in range [" << itor->start.ToString() << " - " << itor->end.ToString() << "], "
3162  << "highest node index is '" << m_rig->free_node - 1 << "'.";
3163 
3164  if (itor->end.Str().empty()) /* If the node is numeric... */
3165  {
3166  msg << " However, this node must be accepted anyway for backwards compatibility."
3167  << " Please fix this as soon as possible.";
3168  end = itor->end.Num();
3169  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3170  }
3171  else
3172  {
3173  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3174  return false;
3175  }
3176  }
3177  else
3178  {
3179  end = static_cast<unsigned int>(result_b);
3180  }
3181 
3182  if (end < start)
3183  {
3184  unsigned int swap = start;
3185  start = end;
3186  end = swap;
3187  }
3188 
3189  for (unsigned int i = start; i <= end; i++)
3190  {
3191  out_node_indices.push_back(i);
3192  }
3193  }
3194  else
3195  {
3196  out_node_indices.push_back(GetNodeIndexOrThrow(itor->start));
3197  }
3198  }
3199  return true;
3200 }
3201 
3202 Rail *RigSpawner::CreateRail(std::vector<RigDef::Node::Range> & node_ranges)
3203 {
3204  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3205 
3206  /* Collect nodes */
3207  std::vector<unsigned int> node_indices;
3208  node_indices.reserve(100);
3209 
3210  CollectNodesFromRanges(node_ranges, node_indices);
3211 
3212  /* Find beams &build rail */
3213  RailBuilder rail_builder; /* rail builder allocates the memory for each rail, it will not free it */
3214  if (node_indices.front() == node_indices.back())
3215  {
3216  rail_builder.loopRail();
3217  }
3218 
3219  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < node_indices.size() - 1; i++)
3220  {
3221  beam_t *beam = FindBeamInRig(node_indices[i], node_indices[i + 1]);
3222  if (beam == nullptr)
3223  {
3224  std::stringstream msg;
3225  msg << "No beam between nodes indexed '" << node_indices[i] << "' and '" << node_indices[i + 1] << "'";
3226  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3227  return nullptr;
3228  }
3229  rail_builder.pushBack(beam);
3230  }
3231 
3232  return rail_builder.getCompletedRail(); /* Transfers memory ownership */
3233 }
3234 
3235 beam_t *RigSpawner::FindBeamInRig(unsigned int node_a_index, unsigned int node_b_index)
3236 {
3237  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3238 
3239  node_t *node_a = & m_rig->nodes[node_a_index];
3240  node_t *node_b = & m_rig->nodes[node_b_index];
3241 
3242  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < static_cast<unsigned int>(m_rig->free_beam); i++)
3243  {
3244  if (
3245  (GetBeam(i).p1 == node_a && GetBeam(i).p2 == node_b)
3246  || (GetBeam(i).p2 == node_a && GetBeam(i).p1 == node_b)
3247  )
3248  {
3249  return & GetBeam(i);
3250  }
3251  }
3252  return nullptr;
3253 }

3255 void RigSpawner::ProcessHook(RigDef::Hook & def)
3256 {
3257  SPAWNER_PROFILE_SCOPED();
3258 
3259  /* Find the node */
3260  node_t *node = GetNodePointer(def.node);
3261  if (node == nullptr)
3262  {
3263  return;
3264  }
3265 
3266  /* Find the hook */
3267  hook_t *hook = nullptr;
3268  std::vector <hook_t>::iterator itor = m_rig->hooks.begin();
3269  for (; itor != m_rig->hooks.end(); itor++)
3270  {
3271  if (itor->hookNode == node)
3272  {
3273  hook = &*itor;
3274  break;
3275  }
3276  }
3277 
3278  if (hook == nullptr)
3279  {
3280  std::stringstream msg;
3281  msg << "Node '" << def.node.ToString() << "' is not a hook-node (not marked with flag 'h'), ignoring...";
3282  AddMessage(Message::TYPE_ERROR, msg.str());
3283  return;
3284  }
3285 
3286  /* Process options */
3287  hook->lockrange = def.option_hook_range;
3288  hook->lockspeed = def.option_speed_coef * HOOK_SPEED_DEFAULT;
3289  hook->maxforce = def.option_max_force;
3290  hook->group = def.option_hookgroup;
3291  hook->lockgroup = def.option_lockgroup;
3292  hook->timer = 0.f; // Hardcoded in BTS_HOOKS
3293  hook->timer_preset = def.option_timer;
3294  hook->beam->commandShort = def.option_minimum_range_meters;
3295  hook->selflock = BITMASK_IS_1(def.flags, RigDef::Hook::FLAG_SELF_LOCK);
3296  hook->nodisable = BITMASK_IS_1(def.flags, RigDef::Hook::FLAG_NO_DISABLE);
3297  hook->is_hook_visible = false;
3298  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.flags, RigDef::Hook::FLAG_AUTO_LOCK))
3299  {
3300  hook->autolock = true;
3301  if (hook->group == -1)
3302  {
3303  hook->group = -2; /* only overwrite hgroup when its still default (-1) */
3304  }
3305  }
3306  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.flags, RigDef::Hook::FLAG_NO_ROPE))
3307  {
3308  hook->beam->bounded = NOSHOCK;
3309  }
3310  if (BITMASK_IS_1(def.flags, RigDef::Hook::FLAG_VISIBLE))
3311  {
3312  hook->is_hook_visible = true;
3313  if (hook->beam->mSceneNode->numAttachedObjects() == 0)
3314  {
3315  hook->beam->mSceneNode->attachObject(hook->beam->mEntity);
3316  }
3317  }
3318 }
